d_gmt":"2018-02-06T17:18:12","slug":"step-1-clone-and-installation","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https://staticsitegenerator.wordpress.com/2018/01/23/step-1-clone-and-installation/","title":{"rendered":"Step 1 &#8211; clone and&nbsp;installation"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>I assume if you&#8217;re already familiar with tools like <a href=\"https://git-scm.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">GIT</a> and NPM. What you need to complete Step 1 is GIT and NPM installed on your computer.</p>\n<p>Start by cloning the &#8220;Startup Package&#8221; from GitHub and install the required packages via npm.</p>\n<pre><code>git clone https://github.com/sjsd/static-site-generator-from-wordpress-rest-api\nnpm install</code></pre>\n<p>You are now done with Step 1.</p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>How to get the code and install the dependencies.</p>\n","protected":false},"author":4320499,"featured_media":21,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[1850],"tags":[],"jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":35,"url":"https://staticsitegenerator.wordpress.com/2018/02/01/step-3-build/","url_meta":{"origin":20,"position":0},"title":"Step 3 - build","date":"1. February 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"Run and build your first static page.","rel":"nofollow","context":"In \"Ukategorisert\"","img":{"src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"revisions":{"count":4,"last_id":38},"featured_media_url":"https://staticsitegenerator.files.wordpress.com/2018/01/pexels-photo.jpg","_links":{"self":[{"href":"https://public-api.wordpress.com/wp/v2/sites/staticsitegenerator.wordpress.com/posts/20"}],"collection":[{"href":"https://public-api.wordpress.com/wp/v2/sites/staticsitegenerator.wordpress.com/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https://public-api.wordpress.com/wp/v2/sites/staticsitegenerator.wordpress.com/types/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https://public-api.wordpress.com/wp/v2/sites/staticsitegenerator.wordpress.com/users/4320499"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https://public-api.wordpress.com/wp/v2/sites/staticsitegenerator.wordpress.com/comments?post=20"}],"version-history":[{"href":"https://public-api.wordpress.com/wp/v2/sites/staticsitegenerator.wordpress.com/posts/20/revisions"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https://public-api.wordpress.com/wp/v2/sites/staticsitegenerator.wordpress.com/media/21"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https://public-api.wordpress.com/wp/v2/sites/staticsitegenerator.wordpress.com/media?parent=20"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https://public-api.wordpress.com/wp/v2/sites/staticsitegenerator.wordpress.com/categories?post=20"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https://public-api.wordpress.com/wp/v2/sites/staticsitegenerator.wordpress.com/tags?post=20"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https://api.w.org/{rel}","templated":true}]}},{"id":9,"date":"2018-01-22T20:28:55","date_gmt":"2018-01-22T19:28:55","guid":{"rendered":"https://staticsitegenerator.wordpress.com/?p=9"},"modified":"2018-02-06T18:20:56","modified_gmt":"2018-02-06T17:20:56","slug":"introduction","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https://staticsitegenerator.wordpress.com/2018/01/22/introduction/","title":{"rendered":"Introduction"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Since you have found your way here, you already have knowledge about static page generation and <a href=\"https://wordpress.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">WordPress</a>. So I will not elaborate on the advantages or disadvantages of static page generation. There already exist a <a href=\"https://www.staticgen.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">trillions generators out there</a> made by genius people and that solves so many things. Plugin for publishing static JSON files from WordPress. There are even <a href=\"https://www.hardypress.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">someone who earns money based on the same idea</a>. We&#8217;ll ignore that they were first and focus on this project.</p>\n<p>Common to many of them is that they either rely on the user to be able to create files and write Markdown. The cool kids these days use headless CMS. With that, there are also a number of advantages and disadvantages.</p>\n<p>Ask yourself or your customers if they can anything about this. No? Do you know WordPress? Yes!</p>\n<p>I based my code on a CMS that is very well known among many: WordPress. I know, I know &#8230; before you chop my head off: By using WordPress.com or somehow camouflage your own WordPress-installation you can / might get rid of many hackers. Most of us know how to use WordPress. Even your customer or grandma!</p>\n<p>I believe using WordPress&#8217; REST API is a great way to get content. My goal is to create a static page generator based on blog posts in WordPress. And maybe other stuff from WordPress. Who knows?!</p>\n<p>I have <del>three</del> two goals for this project:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Learning about Node.js, static page generation, WordPress REST API</li>\n<li>Free and open source</li>\n<li>*<del>Get rich and famous</del></li>\n</ol>\n<p>I will never get rich and famous by doing this. But I will get a lot&#8217;s of questions about why it doesn&#8217;t work on someones computer. I can&#8217;t wait!</p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Introduction to the code and my thoughts about the project.</p>\n","protected":false},"author":4320499,"featured_media":12,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[1850],"tags":[],"jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":7,"url":"https://staticsitegenerator.wordpress.com/2018/01/22/7/","url_meta":{"origin":9,"position":0},"title":"Untitled Post","date":"22. January 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"","rel":"nofollow","context":"","img":{"src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"revisions":{"count":12,"last_id":41},"featured_media_url":"htt